️ Current issues / risks 
1. OCR confidence ≠ parsing confidence 
Your ScoreOcrText() measures: 
• text length 
• presence of dates 
• presence of monetary amounts 
But it does not validate row structure. 
So OCR text can score well but still be un-parseable as transactions. 
2. Bitmap → Pix conversion is lossy & slow 
1     bitmap.Save(ms, ImageFormat.Bmp); 
2     Pix.LoadFromMemory(...) 
This: 
• duplicates memory 
• strips metadata 
• is slower than needed 
3. Entire-page OCR instead of row-aware OCR 
Tesseract is classifying paragraphs, not transactions. 
This is why your output has: 
• duplicated dates 
• merged descriptions 
• misaligned amounts 
4. No OCR whitelist 
Bank statements are highly structured, but Tesseract is unrestricted. 
